    "problemStatement": "After getting lost in Hollywood, ibti decided to give you yet another problem related to permutations.\n\nConsider a permutation PPP of length 2\u22c5N2\\cdot N2\u22c5N.\n\nAn array AAA of size NNN is generated using the permutation PPP, such that the ithi^{th}ith element of the array is a **pair** having value, Ai=(Pi\u200amod\u200aN,P(i+N)\u200amod\u200aN)A_i = (P_i \\bmod N, P_{(i+N)} \\bmod N)Ai\u200b=(Pi\u200bmodN,P(i+N)\u200bmodN).\n\nThe permutation PPP (of length 2\u22c5N2\\cdot N2\u22c5N) is called NNN-beautiful, if, all elements of the array AAA are **distinct**.\n\nGiven integers KKK and MMM, your task is to count the number of iii-beautiful permutations for each 1\u2264i\u2264K1 \\le i \\le K1\u2264i\u2264K.\n\nSince the answers can be large, print them modulo MMM.\n\n\nInput Format\nThe first and only line of the input contains two space-separated integers KKK, MMM - the parameters defined in the statement.\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nPrint KKK space-separated integers, the ithi^{th}ith integer will denote the number of iii-beautiful permutations modulo MMM.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264K\u22642\u22c51051 \\le K \\le 2 \\cdot 10^51\u2264K\u22642\u22c5105",
      "107+19\u2264M\u2264109+710^7 + 19 \\le M \\le 10^9+7107+19\u2264M\u2264109+7",
      "It is guaranteed that MMM is a prime number.",
      "Subtasks",
      "**Subtask 1 (50 points):** 1\u2264K\u22641031 \\leq K \\leq 10^31\u2264K\u2264103",
      "**Subtask 2 (50 points):** No further constraints."
    ],
